reviews.text:
It was our second time we stayed at this hotel since December 2018.  Once again, we are extremely happy with the efficient booking service provided by Ms Debbie Chan.  We booked two rooms this time as we were travelling with our son and daughter-in-law.  We all loved the good location and the comfortable rooms. We certainly will be back again.
We would like to specially thank  Ms Debbie Chan and her staff at the reception desk (Johnny and Ivan), and also the concierge, Vincent for making our stay enjoyable.
Nice hotel, staff is polite and rooms are clean and nice. Fantastic view and close to the metro.
Convenient location. Small rooms but all hotels in HK are small. Nice view if you have seaview. Good price.
For the price, this was a very well located hotel with comfortable rooms and lovely service.
Large rooms with living and 2 bathroom.  Amazing. Nice stuff and very helpful.  Good location near the subway station.  Loved it.

reviews.text: Did not expect anything because the price set was relatively economical, but turned out really surprised us with the quality food and variety. It was not crowded at all with very spacious environment. Wide variety of hot food and really love it. Also, the refilling speed was awesome and much better than lots of so-called five start hotel. Pricing at this range, definitely worth coming again as repeat diners. Highly recommended!

Good selection and quality at affordable prices.  Comfortable spacious setting with friendly service.  Food selection rotated every so often but always have certain types such as curry. Choices include sushi, sashimi, salad bar, meat wagon.  Recomended dishes (when available): Chinese soup of the day, salmon sashimi, broiled shrimps, coffee mousse tarts, beef brisket, and ox tail.

It was our second time we stayed at this hotel since December 2018.  Once again, we are extremely happy with the efficient booking service provided by Ms Debbie Chan.  We booked two rooms this time as we were travelling with our son and daughter-in-law.  We all loved the good location and the comfortable rooms. We certainly will be back again.
We would like to specially thank  Ms Debbie Chan and her staff at the reception desk (Johnny and Ivan), and also the concierge, Vincent for making our stay enjoyable.

星期日自助午餐長者收費大約2百餘元。食物方面大致正常好食。品種都夠及合理。通常切肉會有两種……西冷牛、肉眼牛、羊、德國咸豬手，德國腸等，有時會有两三種，有煎薄餅熱食大约有十一二種，猪，牛羊雞魚都有亦有二三欵熟菜，今次有我最喜歡食的豬脚，冷食有虾、長脚蟹（細）加拿大螺本地东風螺，青口，上次有幾隻大頭虾。不细心就走眼看不到。其他尚有日本魚生三四年欵，切片排列在大碟上及寿司任取，甜點有班cake機小朋友最中意！甜點及生果有一大長枱選擇多。餐廳地方樓高不過不失。待應招呼不錯。不過要预早订位，否則無位。

В июне 2019 останавливались  в отеле L'hotel Causeway Bay Harbour View
Отель просто замечательный. Большрй номер. Хорошая уборка. Отличный завтрак. 
Около отеля станция метро Tin Hau. Автобусные и трамвайные остановки. Обменник. Аптеки маркеты. Отель расположен рядом с парком виктории. Также пешком можно дойти до causewey.
Также рядом с отелем есть хороший плавательный бессейн.
